    "Thomas Manton": "Again, observe that sin is a defilement; it staineth and darkeneth the glory of a man, Mat. xv.\n3. Observe the suitableness of the judgment to the sin; he saith darkness , not fire . Clouds that darken the truth are justly punished with \u2018the mists of darkness for ever;\u2019 see 2 Peter `[char_Peter_Mat_4]` ii.\n3. Again, observe that sin is a defilement; it staineth and darkeneth the glory of a man, Mat. xv.\n3. Observe the suitableness of the judgment to the sin; he saith darkness, not fire. Clouds that darken the truth are justly punished with \u2018the mists of darkness for ever;\u2019 see 2 Peter `[char_Peter_Mat_4]` ii.",
